      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even at low doses, there's still a risk associated with combining St. John's wort and sertraline. St. John's wort can affect liver enzymes which might interfere with the metabolism of sertraline, potentially leading to either decreased efficacy or increased side effects, or even dangerous reactions. It is always safest to consult your doctor before making any changes to your medication plan. Your healthcare provider can thoroughly review your situation and provide alternative strategies to manage your symptoms effectively and safely without risking detrimental interactions.",
      "source": "target",
